<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900926-0075</DOCNO><DOCID>900926-0075.</DOCID><HL>   Hughes Aircraft Joins   Samsung to Pursue   South Korean Contract</HL><DATE>09/26/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   GMH C.SSG FREST GM</CO><IN>AEROSPACE (ARO)COMMUNICATIONS TECHNOLOGY (CMT)</IN><LP>   LOS ANGELES -- Hughes Aircraft Co., a unit of GeneralMotors Corp., and Samsung Group in Seoul, South Korea, saidthey have teamed up to pursue a contract to introducedomestic satellite communications to South Korea.   The company said the South Korean government has said itwants to establish a domestic satellite system with data,voice and video communications and direct-broadcasttelevision capabilities. South Korea is expected to requestproposals in the spring of next year and to award a contractin early 1992.</LP><TEXT>   Hughes is a large manufacturer of commercialcommunications satellites and a supplier of defenseelectronics. Samsung is a conglomerate with interests inelectronics, telecommunications, precision instruments andchemicals.   Hughes said the work will be done through its Space andamp;Communications Group and the Samsung Co. internationaldivision of the Samsung Group. Hughes also said its HughesNetwork Systems subsidiary has signed an agreement makingSamsung its representative in South Korea for sales ofground-station equipment for satellite systems.</TEXT></DOC>